cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DS 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with weakly supervised segmentation using CNNs. It also involves optimization techniques, which makes it relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the computational complexity and stability/convergence issues, which are relevant to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a new approach for approximating Lagrangian optimization, which is related to optimization algorithms and could be relevant to the data structures (cs.DS) sub-category.
